        <descriptionSet>
            <description>On September 2, 1908, astronomer Daniel Morehouse - studying and photographing comets with Edward Emerson Barnard at Yerkes Observatory - discovered a comet near Cassiopeia. Close observation of the comet by Barnard led to speculation that the tails of comets could be affected by solar weather. This image of Comet Morehouse was taken with the Bruce 10-inch telescope at Yerkes Observatory on November 16, 1908.</description>
